01:00:02.970 --> 01:00:06.350 align:middle line:84%
all his skin down, so we had
to pull it up like a sock,

01:00:06.350 --> 01:00:09.510 align:middle line:84%
bandage it with manuka
honey every day,

01:00:09.510 --> 01:00:12.230 align:middle line:84%
fresh manuka honey on every day,
and the whole thing has healed

01:00:12.230 --> 01:00:13.030 align:middle line:90%
completely.

01:00:13.030 --> 01:00:14.250 align:middle line:90%
And vets can't believe it.

01:00:14.250 --> 01:00:21.000 align:middle line:90%


01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:22.300 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm stung.

01:00:22.300 --> 01:00:23.100 align:middle line:90%
I'm stung.

01:00:23.100 --> 01:00:26.000 align:middle line:90%


01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:30.290 align:middle line:84%
And it's pumping the
toxin into my flesh.

01:00:30.290 --> 01:00:32.033 align:middle line:90%
You can see it moving.

01:00:32.033 --> 01:00:33.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to just give
you a demonstration how

01:00:33.950 --> 01:00:35.700 align:middle line:90%
to get them out.

01:00:35.700 --> 01:00:39.030 align:middle line:84%
So you'll just bend your
fingernail back like that,

01:00:39.030 --> 01:00:40.580 align:middle line:90%
and go--

01:00:40.580 --> 01:00:41.670 align:middle line:90%
cut it off.

01:00:41.670 --> 01:00:47.190 align:middle line:84%
The venom from the bee sting is
the same as rattlesnake poison.

01:00:47.190 --> 01:00:49.980 align:middle line:84%
So if you-- the
only thing is it's

01:00:49.980 --> 01:00:52.110 align:middle line:90%
only a little minute amount.

01:00:52.110 --> 01:00:54.930 align:middle line:84%
Rattlesnake bite can
kill you, but, well,

01:00:54.930 --> 01:00:58.350 align:middle line:84%
if you got enough bee stings,
it would kill you too.

01:00:58.350 --> 01:01:03.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Beekeeper, he can
receive 500 stings.

01:01:03.860 --> 01:01:07.740 align:middle line:90%
But more than 500, he can die.

01:01:07.740 --> 01:01:13.230 align:middle line:84%
So we have to be in very
deep respect about bee.

01:01:13.230 --> 01:01:15.120 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

01:01:15.120 --> 01:01:22.500 align:middle line:90%


01:01:22.500 --> 01:01:24.665 align:middle line:84%
To be a beekeeper
is a kind of art.

01:01:24.665 --> 01:01:29.990 align:middle line:90%


01:01:29.990 --> 01:01:33.950 align:middle line:84%
If you are a yogi,
if you practice yoga,

01:01:33.950 --> 01:01:38.180 align:middle line:84%
naturally you can
be a beekeeper,

01:01:38.180 --> 01:01:41.540 align:middle line:90%
because you have to be quiet.

01:01:41.540 --> 01:01:45.700 align:middle line:90%
You have to explore your soul.

01:01:45.700 --> 01:01:48.370 align:middle line:90%
Bees, life and death.

01:01:48.370 --> 01:01:51.640 align:middle line:84%
>> What's particularly
unfortunate is that honeybees

01:01:51.640 --> 01:01:54.850 align:middle line:84%
are often blamed for stings
that are inflicted by other

01:01:54.850 --> 01:01:56.020 align:middle line:90%
Hymenopterans.

01:01:56.020 --> 01:01:59.320 align:middle line:84%
To an entomologist, a
yellow jacket is a wasp.

01:01:59.320 --> 01:02:00.700 align:middle line:90%
It looks nothing like a bee.

01:02:00.700 --> 01:02:03.700 align:middle line:84%
Bees are sort of
brownish and fuzzy.

01:02:03.700 --> 01:02:06.040 align:middle line:84%
Yellow jackets are yellow
and black and shiny.

01:02:06.040 --> 01:02:09.100 align:middle line:84%
Different behavior,
different gestalt,

01:02:09.100 --> 01:02:14.230 align:middle line:84%
but the vast majority of
non-entomologists, people

01:02:14.230 --> 01:02:20.290 align:middle line:84%
are either unwilling to or
unable to differentiate.

01:02:20.290 --> 01:02:24.460 align:middle line:84%
So bees get a lot of bad
press that is undeserved.

01:02:24.460 --> 01:02:26.692 align:middle line:84%
>> Can you clip this
little branch there first?

01:02:26.692 --> 01:02:27.650 align:middle line:90%
>> This one right here?

01:02:27.650 --> 01:02:28.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:02:28.110 --> 01:02:29.140 align:middle line:90%
>> It's about to go.

01:02:29.140 --> 01:02:30.916 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

01:02:30.916 --> 01:02:31.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Oops.

01:02:31.880 --> 01:02:36.230 align:middle line:90%


01:02:36.230 --> 01:02:40.900 align:middle line:84%
>> A swarm, as much as
people don't like it,

01:02:40.900 --> 01:02:47.650 align:middle line:84%
is a natural way of procreation,
of guaranteeing that more

01:02:47.650 --> 01:02:50.360 align:middle line:90%
colonies of bees are there.

01:02:50.360 --> 01:02:54.440 align:middle line:84%
And at the right time when the
new queens are ready to emerge,

01:02:54.440 --> 01:02:59.530 align:middle line:84%
the old queen, with almost
half of the entire workers,

01:02:59.530 --> 01:03:01.710 align:middle line:90%
will leave the hive.

01:03:01.710 --> 01:03:06.660 align:middle line:84%
They swirl around in the
circumference of maybe 50 feet.

01:03:06.660 --> 01:03:10.260 align:middle line:84%
And then the queen
lands and alights

01:03:10.260 --> 01:03:13.860 align:middle line:84%
on maybe a branch, and the
rest of those swarm bees

01:03:13.860 --> 01:03:15.390 align:middle line:90%
gather in a cluster.

01:03:15.390 --> 01:03:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And they hang there
until they are either

01:03:19.110 --> 01:03:23.820 align:middle line:84%
taken by the beekeeper
or they find a new home.

01:03:23.820 --> 01:03:27.070 align:middle line:90%


01:03:27.070 --> 01:03:30.450 align:middle line:84%
So the commercial
or the average hobby

01:03:30.450 --> 01:03:34.590 align:middle line:90%
beekeeper prevent swarming.

01:03:34.590 --> 01:03:40.230 align:middle line:84%
And we have taken that
joy, that joie de vivre,

01:03:40.230 --> 01:03:46.740 align:middle line:84%
that wonderful invigorating
activity away from them.

01:03:46.740 --> 01:03:49.830 align:middle line:84%
For the honeybee to
regain her health,

01:03:49.830 --> 01:03:54.600 align:middle line:84%
I think we also have to see
that the swarming is allowed

01:03:54.600 --> 01:03:55.920 align:middle line:90%
again as much as possible.

01:03:55.920 --> 01:04:06.800 align:middle line:90%


01:04:06.800 --> 01:04:09.830 align:middle line:84%
>> When somebody calls, and
I'm on lists all over the place

01:04:09.830 --> 01:04:10.910 align:middle line:90%
for swarms--

01:04:10.910 --> 01:04:12.470 align:middle line:90%
oh, this is great--

01:04:12.470 --> 01:04:15.020 align:middle line:84%
I actually go to the hives
where people are freaked out

01:04:15.020 --> 01:04:17.090 align:middle line:90%
and they're afraid.

01:04:17.090 --> 01:04:21.050 align:middle line:84%
That to me is like,
uh-oh, hive in danger.

01:04:21.050 --> 01:04:23.425 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people call
an exterminator.

01:04:23.425 --> 01:04:25.550 align:middle line:84%
They really think that the
bees are going to attack

01:04:25.550 --> 01:04:27.310 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

01:04:27.310 --> 01:04:32.120 align:middle line:84%
They're at their most
docile at that time.

01:04:32.120 --> 01:04:35.420 align:middle line:84%
Exterminators come
and they poison them.

01:04:35.420 --> 01:04:38.890 align:middle line:84%
I tell people that you're
seeing a miracle of nature.

01:04:38.890 --> 01:04:41.980 align:middle line:84%
This is a force of nature
come and landed on your tree.

01:04:41.980 --> 01:04:44.240 align:middle line:84%
Bee hive is just simply
moving to a new home.

01:04:44.240 --> 01:04:47.910 align:middle line:90%


01:04:47.910 --> 01:04:50.480 align:middle line:84%
The woman I was helping,
she had just taken my class,

01:04:50.480 --> 01:04:52.700 align:middle line:84%
and she didn't have
any bees before.

01:04:52.700 --> 01:04:54.980 align:middle line:90%
And often I say get a swarm.

01:04:54.980 --> 01:04:55.860 align:middle line:90%
Don't buy bees.

01:04:55.860 --> 01:04:56.660 align:middle line:90%
That's commercial.

01:04:56.660 --> 01:04:59.810 align:middle line:90%
That's cattle ranching bees.

01:04:59.810 --> 01:05:02.270 align:middle line:84%
And I invite them to come
with me on a swarm call,

01:05:02.270 --> 01:05:05.450 align:middle line:84%
and I help people get set
up with their first hive.

01:05:05.450 --> 01:05:06.680 align:middle line:90%
It's so wonderful.

01:05:06.680 --> 01:05:08.212 align:middle line:84%
Then they get to
handle the bees,

01:05:08.212 --> 01:05:09.420 align:middle line:90%
and they get to be with them.

01:05:09.420 --> 01:05:12.355 align:middle line:84%
It isn't just sticking them in
a box and letting them grow.

01:05:12.355 --> 01:05:13.730 align:middle line:84%
So they get to
interact with them

01:05:13.730 --> 01:05:15.424 align:middle line:90%
right from the very beginning.

01:05:15.424 --> 01:05:20.860 align:middle line:90%


01:05:20.860 --> 01:05:23.250 align:middle line:84%
You could see how
happy she was, and she

01:05:23.250 --> 01:05:25.440 align:middle line:90%
started singing with the bees.

01:05:25.440 --> 01:05:29.790 align:middle line:84%
She was feeling into them,
and she'll be a good bee mama.

01:05:29.790 --> 01:05:30.780 align:middle line:90%
>> I can't express it.

01:05:30.780 --> 01:05:35.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm just-- I'm
like a little kid.

01:05:35.990 --> 01:05:38.580 align:middle line:84%
It's like I got my first bicycle
or something, I don't know.

01:05:38.580 --> 01:05:42.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm just so excited to work
with them, and learn with them,

01:05:42.220 --> 01:05:43.130 align:middle line:90%
and yeah.

01:05:43.130 --> 01:05:52.212 align:middle line:90%


01:05:52.212 --> 01:05:55.680 align:middle line:90%
>> I wonder if bees paint.

01:05:55.680 --> 01:05:56.870 align:middle line:90%
And if they do, how?

01:05:56.870 --> 01:05:59.150 align:middle line:84%
>> My name is Wisteria, and
I'm a backyard beekeeper

01:05:59.150 --> 01:06:01.010 align:middle line:90%
in Portland, Oregon.

01:06:01.010 --> 01:06:09.250 align:middle line:84%
And we are building beehives
and painting bee boxes.

01:06:09.250 --> 01:06:13.030 align:middle line:84%
I've got my friends and family
and members of the Bee Project

01:06:13.030 --> 01:06:13.840 align:middle line:90%
here.

01:06:13.840 --> 01:06:15.520 align:middle line:90%
We're tasting mead.

01:06:15.520 --> 01:06:16.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Which is delicious.

01:06:16.490 --> 01:06:18.730 align:middle line:84%
It has a little bit
of a sparkle to it.

01:06:18.730 --> 01:06:21.100 align:middle line:84%
>> And just sharing with
families from Portland what

01:06:21.100 --> 01:06:22.150 align:middle line:90%
beekeeping is all about.

01:06:22.150 --> 01:06:33.630 align:middle line:90%


01:06:33.630 --> 01:06:36.850 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm a rooftop beekeeper
in New York City.

01:06:36.850 --> 01:06:39.880 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a third
generation beekeeper.

01:06:39.880 --> 01:06:41.470 align:middle line:90%
It's illegal here to keep bees.

01:06:41.470 --> 01:06:47.090 align:middle line:90%


01:06:47.090 --> 01:06:48.520 align:middle line:90%
It kind of scares me.

01:06:48.520 --> 01:06:49.820 align:middle line:90%
It worries me a little bit.

01:06:49.820 --> 01:06:53.360 align:middle line:90%


01:06:53.360 --> 01:06:57.020 align:middle line:84%
I really would like
to keep my bees.

01:06:57.020 --> 01:07:00.875 align:middle line:84%
We're really just trying to do
something simple for nature.

01:07:00.875 --> 01:07:06.080 align:middle line:90%


01:07:06.080 --> 01:07:07.670 align:middle line:84%
This is really a
crazy moment here.

01:07:07.670 --> 01:07:11.240 align:middle line:84%
As we're doing this,
there's a swarm of bees.

01:07:11.240 --> 01:07:13.280 align:middle line:84%
They look like they're
going into that tree

01:07:13.280 --> 01:07:15.980 align:middle line:84%
right there, which is not--
it's just completely bizarre.

01:07:15.980 --> 01:07:17.580 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure where
they came from,

01:07:17.580 --> 01:07:19.335 align:middle line:90%
and they're coming closer.

01:07:19.335 --> 01:07:21.960 align:middle line:84%
It does look like there they are
sort of aiming right in there.

01:07:21.960 --> 01:07:23.043 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, they totally are.

01:07:23.043 --> 01:07:24.090 align:middle line:90%
>> That's crazy.

01:07:24.090 --> 01:07:26.503 align:middle line:84%
>> I've never quite
seen this happening.

01:07:26.503 --> 01:07:30.670 align:middle line:90%


01:07:30.670 --> 01:07:33.870 align:middle line:84%
>> I think you guys brought
that mojo, honestly.

01:07:33.870 --> 01:07:36.482 align:middle line:84%
Only in the Bronx, baby, are
you going to find a swarm.

01:07:36.482 --> 01:07:42.748 align:middle line:90%


01:07:42.748 --> 01:07:44.885 align:middle line:90%
>> Legalize beekeeping.

01:07:44.885 --> 01:07:47.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Give the bees a chance.

01:07:47.360 --> 01:07:49.835 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERING]

01:07:49.835 --> 01:07:50.825 align:middle line:90%


01:07:50.825 --> 01:07:58.250 align:middle line:84%
>> All we are saying
is give bees a chance.

01:07:58.250 --> 01:08:00.724 align:middle line:90%
>> Legalize beekeeping.

01:08:00.724 --> 01:08:02.125 align:middle line:90%
>> Give the bees a chance.

01:08:02.125 --> 01:08:06.340 align:middle line:90%


01:08:06.340 --> 01:08:08.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Beekeeping, the vital
practice of managing

01:08:08.720 --> 01:08:11.210 align:middle line:84%
and maintaining honeybee
colonies for pollination

01:08:11.210 --> 01:08:14.240 align:middle line:84%
and honey production, is a
banned practice in New York

01:08:14.240 --> 01:08:15.260 align:middle line:90%
City.

01:08:15.260 --> 01:08:17.569 align:middle line:84%
This ban is outdated
and detrimental

01:08:17.569 --> 01:08:19.880 align:middle line:84%
to the health and well-being
of our urban environment

01:08:19.880 --> 01:08:21.410 align:middle line:90%
and our community.

01:08:21.410 --> 01:08:23.120 align:middle line:84%
This bill needs
our support, and I

01:08:23.120 --> 01:08:26.240 align:middle line:84%
encourage you to call your city
council representative today

01:08:26.240 --> 01:08:29.060 align:middle line:84%
and encourage them to support
Councilman Yassky's bill.

01:08:29.060 --> 01:08:32.630 align:middle line:84%
>> One of my neighbors, probably
because they were uninformed

01:08:32.630 --> 01:08:38.930 align:middle line:84%
and scared maybe, reported the
hive to the health department.

01:08:38.930 --> 01:08:42.500 align:middle line:84%
And as a result, I was served
with a notice of violation,

01:08:42.500 --> 01:08:46.710 align:middle line:84%
and I have to appear at
a hearing in 15 minutes.

01:08:46.710 --> 01:08:49.859 align:middle line:84%
>> If she has a child, and
sees, as she pointed out,

01:08:49.859 --> 01:08:51.180 align:middle line:90%
this swarm of bees--

01:08:51.180 --> 01:08:55.080 align:middle line:84%
>> If beekeeping is done
properly, it's a safe activity.

01:08:55.080 --> 01:08:56.450 align:middle line:90%
This solves both problems.

01:08:56.450 --> 01:08:58.500 align:middle line:84%
Lets people who want
to do it, do it,

01:08:58.500 --> 01:08:59.939 align:middle line:84%
and makes sure
that those who are

01:08:59.939 --> 01:09:03.240 align:middle line:84%
going to engage in this
beekeeping do it safely.

01:09:03.240 --> 01:09:06.180 align:middle line:84%
>> So here we have a wonderful
opportunity to do what other

01:09:06.180 --> 01:09:07.590 align:middle line:90%
great cities have done.

01:09:07.590 --> 01:09:11.260 align:middle line:84%
Legalize bees, allow
for honey production,

01:09:11.260 --> 01:09:14.819 align:middle line:84%
whether it's on a tiny
rooftop or a small garden,

01:09:14.819 --> 01:09:18.090 align:middle line:84%
and build the sustainability
movement bee by bee.

01:09:18.090 --> 01:09:27.410 align:middle line:90%


01:09:27.410 --> 01:09:28.479 align:middle line:90%
>> --honey festival.

01:09:28.479 --> 01:09:33.020 align:middle line:84%
There will be tastings, and
jugglers, and demonstrations,

01:09:33.020 --> 01:09:35.883 align:middle line:84%
so you should definitely come
and pick up your local honey

01:09:35.883 --> 01:09:37.362 align:middle line:90%
there.

01:09:37.362 --> 01:09:40.320 align:middle line:84%
And all the restaurants
across New York City

01:09:40.320 --> 01:09:42.785 align:middle line:84%
are participating
in New York Nectar.

01:09:42.785 --> 01:09:54.140 align:middle line:90%


01:09:54.140 --> 01:09:58.490 align:middle line:84%
>> So I'm a beekeeper here
at the Center for Discovery.

01:09:58.490 --> 01:10:03.580 align:middle line:84%
I just had this sense that I
had this calling to do service.

01:10:03.580 --> 01:10:04.690 align:middle line:90%
So I'm at home.

01:10:04.690 --> 01:10:05.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm in heaven here.

01:10:05.680 --> 01:10:08.710 align:middle line:90%


01:10:08.710 --> 01:10:11.020 align:middle line:84%
One of the most amazing
things about the farm

01:10:11.020 --> 01:10:13.900 align:middle line:84%
is that we're working with
people with disabilities.

01:10:13.900 --> 01:10:16.672 align:middle line:84%
But by working with them
and integrating them

01:10:16.672 --> 01:10:18.380 align:middle line:84%
into our farm-raised
program, they really

01:10:18.380 --> 01:10:20.370 align:middle line:84%
become individuals
with abilities.

01:10:20.370 --> 01:10:26.121 align:middle line:90%


01:10:26.121 --> 01:10:29.070 align:middle line:90%
Nice work.

01:10:29.070 --> 01:10:33.200 align:middle line:84%
People with autism have this
innate affinity for nature.

01:10:33.200 --> 01:10:36.160 align:middle line:84%
And so by working outside,
they're just-- they're at home.

01:10:36.160 --> 01:10:39.920 align:middle line:90%


01:10:39.920 --> 01:10:41.920 align:middle line:84%
So when I think about
colony collapse disorder,

01:10:41.920 --> 01:10:45.040 align:middle line:84%
I really hope that
we can, as a society,

01:10:45.040 --> 01:10:46.900 align:middle line:84%
have a connection
with nature instead

01:10:46.900 --> 01:10:50.190 align:middle line:90%
of a disconnect with nature.

01:10:50.190 --> 01:10:53.010 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that I
really enjoy about the bees

01:10:53.010 --> 01:10:56.100 align:middle line:84%
is that they all have this
really strong sense of mission.

01:10:56.100 --> 01:10:58.020 align:middle line:84%
It's not about
individual advantage.

01:10:58.020 --> 01:11:01.030 align:middle line:90%
It's not about getting ahead.

01:11:01.030 --> 01:11:02.310 align:middle line:90%
They take on different tasks.

01:11:02.310 --> 01:11:04.950 align:middle line:84%
Like they might start off
as a housekeeper, and then

01:11:04.950 --> 01:11:06.930 align:middle line:90%
a nurse bee.

01:11:06.930 --> 01:11:09.250 align:middle line:84%
Much like we have
different roles here.

01:11:09.250 --> 01:11:15.180 align:middle line:84%
We have integration specialists,
and skills trainers.

01:11:15.180 --> 01:11:17.880 align:middle line:84%
All sorts of people
coming together as a team

01:11:17.880 --> 01:11:19.920 align:middle line:84%
to provide a really
rich and meaningful life

01:11:19.920 --> 01:11:22.870 align:middle line:90%
for our residents here.

01:11:22.870 --> 01:11:25.020 align:middle line:84%
Our job is to create
a family for them

01:11:25.020 --> 01:11:28.050 align:middle line:84%
and to build a community that
they can really thrive in,

01:11:28.050 --> 01:11:30.420 align:middle line:84%
and where they can find
their own niche to really

01:11:30.420 --> 01:11:32.730 align:middle line:84%
be the individual
that they really are.

01:11:32.730 --> 01:11:41.310 align:middle line:90%


01:11:41.310 --> 01:11:44.240 align:middle line:84%
If you take a single
bee out of a hive,

01:11:44.240 --> 01:11:46.130 align:middle line:84%
it actually can't
live on its own.

01:11:46.130 --> 01:11:50.210 align:middle line:84%
It's biologically
dependent upon community.

01:11:50.210 --> 01:11:53.343 align:middle line:84%
And even though some humans
can survive on their own,

01:11:53.343 --> 01:11:55.385 align:middle line:84%
